      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "review-note",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "kind": "informational",
          "level": "none",
          "guid": "mrxfwl182z66e1pb",
          "message": {
            "text": "The ticket proposed a new hard rule banning conditional siblings before each() lists, but KF-377's fix landed in the same unreleased version — the shape is now fully supported and regression-tested, so a hard rule would steer AI assistants into wrapping banners in pointless stable containers on current kerf. Scoped down to a version-scoped diagnosing row (mirrored in cursorrules + usage-guide) so assistants working against apps pinned to kerfjs ≤ 2.0.1 can still recognize the symptom and apply the wrap-or-upgrade fix. The dev-warning idea (item 3) became KF-379 — with the fix, anchor loss is recoverable, so the warning's value shifts to surfacing silent row-state loss on the self-heal path.",
            "markdown": "The ticket proposed a new hard rule banning conditional siblings before each() lists, but KF-377's fix landed in the same unreleased version — the shape is now fully supported and regression-tested, so a hard rule would steer AI assistants into wrapping banners in pointless stable containers on current kerf. Scoped down to a version-scoped diagnosing row (mirrored in cursorrules + usage-guide) so assistants working against apps pinned to kerfjs ≤ 2.0.1 can still recognize the symptom and apply the wrap-or-upgrade fix. The dev-warning idea (item 3) became KF-379 — with the fix, anchor loss is recoverable, so the warning's value shifts to surfacing silent row-state loss on the self-heal path."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "kerf.claude-skill.md"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 183,
                  "endLine": 183,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "| Keyed `each()` list suddenly renders zero rows — only its `<!--kf-list:N-->` marker — with no errors, and it never recovers (kerfjs ≤ 2.0.1) | A conditionally-rendered sibling BEFORE the list (possibly higher in the tree, e.g. an error banner) was removed that render; older kerfjs rebuilt the shifted list container from the template, permanently detaching the list's internal binding | Upgrade kerfjs (fixed after 2.0.1 — the morph now moves the shifted container up in place, keeping node identity). On older versions, keep the structure before the list stable: wrap the conditional in an always-present container (`<div class=\"banners\">{cond ? <div/> : ''}</div>`) |"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "tags": [
              "rationale"
            ]
          },
          "workItemUris": [
            "KF-378"
          ],
          "partialFingerprints": {
            "prNoteAnchor/v1": "7685292f548e7d035c8a59050d983c56"
          }
        }
